reviewText: High Chaparral Season Four none of the cds were recorded on. The discs were completely blank. PLEASE REPLACE

High Chaparral is a terrific western series, one of my favorites. However, one disc in season 1 failed to play and all discs in season 4 were defective as they would only play 2 out of the 4 episodes.
Had to return.  DVD will not run. Tried to use two different DVDs.  First 3 seasons ran perfectly
I have not had a chance to watch the DVD's until tonight..None of them work..They all say there is no playback

season 4 is noted rated for the U.S. My dvd player, as well as my son's dvd player reject the discs as not configured in the U.S.  It is,for all practical reasons, useless. What do we do now?  P.S. Season three works just fine & is quite a great trip back to the 70's Westerns.
Will tis dvd ever be released here in America?????I would love to own it and i do have a region free dvd player but would rather it be where I could watch it on and American dvd player.
I am glad someone had this for sale.  Completed my High Chaparral collection and now I can watch all the seasons in order.
